# User Survey: Safety & Governance Needs for AI Livestream Agents

## Introduction
We are students at UIUC working on a short research project (about **2 minutes**, **4 sections**, **13 questions**) to understand the real challenges creators face when using AI agents or AI VTubers in livestream environments.

Our goal is to help AI VTubers (e.g., Neuro-sama–style interactive agents) develop **more safely, more stably, and with better control**, especially when dealing with fast-moving chats, risky interactions, and adversarial viewers.

Our prototype system, **C-A-B**, aims to:
1. reduce manipulation risks (users tricking the AI)  
2. prevent multi-turn safety failures (AI becoming unsafe over time)  
3. provide creators more transparency and control  
4. automatically stress-test agents before going live  

All responses are anonymous. Thank you for your support!

